\pard\widctlpar\sa160\sl252\slmult1\par
\b Alan Nixon\par
\b0 Life Member since May 2015 \b\par

\pard\widctlpar\sl252\slmult1\b0 Alan has been Secretary of North Queensland Ensembles Inc. and Barrier Reef Orchestra for eight years. He is a former Commonwealth Government officer mainly in the Commonwealth Employment Service. Prior to retirement he was the Departments Zone Manager for North Queensland. Nixon expertise has served the Orchestra well. He was also Secretary at the time when we employed our first Orchestra Manager.  Nixon has a background in community service having been both Australian Jaycees and Rotary. He has also had experience as an actor, producer, and Committee member with several theatre groups across the state. \par

\pard\widctlpar\sa160\sl252\slmult1\b\par
Stephen Frewen-Lord \par

\pard\widctlpar\sl252\slmult1\b0 Life member since May 2015\par
Stephen has been involved with the Barrier Reef Orchestra since its establishment. He played as concert master in the Orchestra\rquote s Inaugural Concert in 2000. Since then, he has missed few concerts and has been concert master for many other concerts. When Stephen was not rehearsing he was attending many other ensembles in Townsville. He manages and plays with the Melaleuca String Quartet, directed Strings Non Troppo, and plays in Double Play (a guitar/violin duo). Stephen has had regular involvement with the Mulkadee Arts Festival, and performs regularly in community events. This includes: Eco Fiesta, Riverfest, Heritage Day and Stable on the Strand. In his role as concert master over the past 15 years, Stephen has enjoyed many discussions with guest conductors concerning the artistic direction of the Orchestra. As a string teacher, he has encouraged many young players who share the same passion for music to become members of the Orchestra. Stephen is looking forward to passing on his position to the next BRO concert master. \par
\f0\fs20\line Carol Dall\rquote Osto \par
Life Member since July 2010\f1\fs22\par
Carol has been a leading figure in music performances in Townsville for many years, even though she lived in Ingham until the 2000s when she moved to Townsville. Carol is a piano teacher, accompanist, and musical director of the Australia Concerto and Vocal Competition which she has led since 1991. She was the chairperson of the North Queensland Ensembles Committee (the parent organisation for the Orchestra), a positon she held until 2003.   \par

\pard\widctlpar\sa160\sl252\slmult1\f0\fs20\par
Jenny Carr\par
Life member since July 2010\par
After coming to Australia in the early 70s Carr instantly became an integral part of the Townsville music scene as a pianist and instrumental music teacher. In 1998, the decision to establish a community orchestra was made, Carr worked as a librarian, performer, and for many years a manager. In conjunction with Donna McMahan and Susan Linge (from the Civic Theatre), they arranged a series of concerts for the emerging Orchestra. Carr was a substitute pianist when the Orchestra was short. As manager, she was involved in all aspects of the Orchestra, including music and attendances. In later years, Carr worked as Adjudicator\rquote s Assistant for the Australian Vocal and Concerto Competition. \par
Donna McMahon\par
Life Member since July 2010\par
Donna has been a leader of the Townsville music community since she arrived in 1973 fresh from the Conservatorium to teach strings for Education Queensland. Until 2009 she has also been involved with the Townsville Youth Orchestra, the Australian String Teachers\rquote  Association, the Australian Concerto & Vocal Competition, and lately of course the Barrier Reef Orchestra. Apart from being one of the prime movers in the formation of the BRO, she has been performer, rehearsal conductor, musical advisor, & visiting conductor liaison. In 2009, she was rehearsal conductor, played with the orchestra, and managed the music library. She recently graduated with a Masters Degree in Music from James Cook University.\b\f1\fs22\par
\b0 David Pearse\par
Life Member since June 2006\par
\f0\fs20 David was heavily involved with the Townsville music scene from the 1970s, including the formation of the BRO in 1999. He was made a Life Member by the Committee in June 2006, when he and his wife Elizabeth left Townsville to live in Canberra.\f1\fs22\par
